UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Pharmaplast Ag Foam Dressings (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p>The <strong>Pharmaplast Ag Foam Dressings</strong> represent an advanced innovation in the field of clinical wound care. Designed with a polyurethane foam integrating silver ions, this dressing offers exceptional biocompatibility, ensuring optimal interaction with the patient''s skin. The integrated silver ions play a crucial role in reducing bacterial load, thus minimizing the risk of infections on and around the wound and promoting faster and more efficient healing.</p><p>The multiple dimensions of these dressings allow ergonomic adaptation to various shapes and sizes of wounds encountered in clinical settings, offering a tailored solution for every care need. Despite its non-sterility, this product ensures a favorable healing environment due to its high absorption capacity and effective management of exudates from acute or chronic wounds, thus enhancing patient comfort and reducing the frequency of dressing changes.</p><p>Each of these dressings is carefully individually wrapped, ensuring product quality and protection until use. Certified with the CE mark, it complies with the most rigorous standards of European safety and performance requirements. Its three-year shelf life attests to its exceptional robustness and durability, providing a reliable and long-lasting solution for healthcare professionals.</p><table class="min-w-full border-collapse"><thead><tr><th class="border px-4 py-2">Specification</th><th class="border px-4 py-2">Detail</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border px-4 py-2">Material</td><td class="border px-4 py-2">Polyurethane foam with silver ions</td></tr><tr><td class="border px-4 py-2">Dimensions</td><td class="border px-4 py-2">Multi-sizes suitable for clinical needs</td></tr><tr><td class="border px-4 py-2">Sterilization</td><td class="border px-4 py-2">Non-sterile</td></tr><tr><td class="border px-4 py-2">CE / ISO Compliance</td><td class="border px-4 py-2">CE Marked</td></tr><tr><td class="border px-4 py-2">Clinical Use</td><td class="border px-4 py-2">Absorption and management of wound exudates</td></tr><tr><td class="border px-4 py-2">Features</td><td class="border px-4 py-2">Individually wrapped, long shelf life</td></tr></tbody></table>' WHERE id = 568;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Intubation Tube with Cuff (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p>The Intubation Tube with Cuff is designed to ensure safety and comfort during tracheal intubation procedures. Made from <strong>medical-grade PVC</strong>, this tube offers excellent biocompatibility to minimize adverse reactions. It features a cuff that ensures stable positioning and effective airway sealing, which is crucial for hospital interventions.</p>
<p>This device achieves a high level of safety through <strong>ethylene oxide (EO) sterilization</strong>, compliant with European health standards. Each tube is meticulously packed in individual sterile blisters to maintain optimal aseptic conditions until use. The variety of available sizes allows perfect adaptation to different clinical needs, ranging from 6.0 to 11.0 mm in diameter.</p>
<p>The advanced ergonomics of the tube are highlighted by a reinforced cut tip, facilitating atraumatic insertion while reducing the risk of tissue injury. With these features, this medical instrument aligns with the rigorous demands of healthcare professionals, ensuring safe, effective, and comfortable clinical use.</p>
