UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Left Selective Intubation Tube Kit Ch26', description_en = '<p class="text-xl font-semibold">The Left Selective Intubation Tube Kit Ch26 is designed to meet the rigorous demands of modern anesthesia procedures. This advanced medical device is made from medical-grade PVC, a material known for its optimal biocompatibility and flexibility, allowing for secure and comfortable intubation. The atraumatic beveled tip design ensures smooth insertion, minimizing the risk of trauma to the sensitive airway tissues.</p><p class="text-xl font-semibold">This kit is sterilized using ethylene oxide (EO), ensuring maximum asepsis for each application. The CE certification of this product attests to its compliance with European safety and efficacy standards, making this kit a trusted choice for healthcare professionals in demanding clinical environments. It is designed for pulmonary selective intubation, specifically targeting the left lung, an indispensable asset in complex operative settings requiring differential ventilation.</p><p class="text-xl font-semibold">Individually and sterilized packaged, each unit of the Left Selective Intubation Tube Kit Ch26 is ready for use, thereby optimizing workflow in healthcare facilities. This innovative product is designed for professionals seeking the quality and performance of a high-end medical device, ensuring easy handling thanks to its ergonomically designed features for clinical effectiveness.</p><table class="min-w-full border-collapse"><thead><tr><th class="border-b-2 border-gray-300 py-2">Specification</th><th class="border-b-2 border-gray-300 py-2">Detail</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border-b-2 border-gray-200 py-2">Material</td><td class="border-b-2 border-gray-200 py-2">Medical-grade PVC</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-2 border-gray-200 py-2">Sterilization</td><td class="border-b-2 border-gray-200 py-2">Ethylene oxide (EO)</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-2 border-gray-200 py-2">Compliance</td><td class="border-b-2 border-gray-200 py-2">CE Certification</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-2 border-gray-200 py-2">Clinical Use</td><td class="border-b-2 border-gray-200 py-2">Pulmonary selective intubation</td></tr><tr><td class="border-b-2 border-gray-200 py-2">Features</td><td class="border-b-2 border-gray-200 py-2">Beveled atraumatic tip</td></tr></tbody></table>' WHERE id = 41;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Fast Track Laryngeal Mask (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p>The <strong>Fast Track Laryngeal Mask</strong>, SKU LMA135130, is a highly sophisticated medical device, intended for professional single-use. Made from high-quality <em>medical-grade silicone</em>, this mask is designed to ensure optimal biocompatibility while providing superior patient comfort. Its ergonomic design allows for easy and atraumatic insertion, minimizing the risk of trauma to the airway.</p><p>Primarily used in demanding clinical settings, this device is sterilized using <em>ethylene oxide (EO)</em> ensuring uncompromised sterility. The Fast Track Laryngeal Mask ensures heightened safety and effectiveness due to its strict compliance with <strong>CE</strong> standards, reflecting rigorous manufacturing and testing criteria. Individually packaged, this product is ready for use and suitable for a variety of medical situations.</p><p>Available in <em>adjustable multi-sizes</em>, the <strong>Fast Track Laryngeal Mask</strong> adapts to different patient morphologies, providing efficient sealing. This flexibility in sizing makes the device particularly versatile and indispensable for healthcare professionals seeking reliable tools tailored to every clinical need. With its <strong>ergonomic design</strong>, the mask facilitates rapid and secure intubation, consolidating its place in modern medical environments.</p><table class="min-w-full bg-white border border-gray-300"><thead><tr><th class="px-4 py-2 border-b">Feature</th><th class="px-4 py-2 border-b">Details</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b">Material</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b">Medical-grade silicone</td></tr><tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b">Sterilization</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b">Ethylene oxide (EO)</td></tr><tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b">Compliance</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b">CE Certification</td></tr><tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b">Clinical Use</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b">Professional single-use</td></tr><tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b">Features</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b">Ergonomic design for easy insertion, adjustable multi-sizes</td></tr></tbody></table>' WHERE id = 43;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Dermatological Excision Kit', description_en = '<p>The Dermatological Excision Kit, reference KIT-DERM-001, is designed to meet the highest standards for healthcare professionals in dermatological procedures. Each kit is meticulously assembled using high-quality materials to ensure optimal performance and enhanced safety. The primary material used, 304 Stainless Steel, is renowned for its exceptional biocompatibility, ensuring minimal interaction with skin tissues while offering remarkable strength and durability.</p><p>The ethylene oxide (EO) sterilization guarantees that every component in the kit is completely free from microbial contamination, allowing for immediate and worry-free use in the operating room. Specifically designed for single use, this kit significantly reduces the risk of nosocomial infection, thus adhering to stringent CE compliance standards.</p><p>Ergonomically and atraumatically designed, this kit includes a No. 15 blade scalpel, ideal for precise and controlled incisions. The 7.5 x 7.5 cm gauzes provide high absorption capacity, essential for maintaining optimal conditions throughout the procedure. This product positions itself as an indispensable tool for dermatologists committed to delivering superior care to their patients.</p><table class="min-w-full bg-white border border-gray-200"><thead><tr class="bg-gray-50"><th class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">Specification</th><th class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">Details</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">Material</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">304 Stainless Steel</td></tr><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">Sterilization</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">Ethylene oxide (EO)</td></tr><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">Compliance</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">CE Compliance</td></tr><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">Clinical Use</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">Single use</td></tr><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">Features</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">No. 15 blade scalpel, 7.5 x 7.5 cm gauzes</td></tr></tbody></table>' WHERE id = 10001;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Coloplast Easicath Male Catheter (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p>The <strong>Coloplast Easicath Male Catheter (Multi-Sizes)</strong> is a state-of-the-art medical device designed to offer an efficient and comfortable urinary catheterization alternative. Made from high-quality <em>medical-grade silicone</em>, this product ensures <strong>exceptional biocompatibility</strong>, minimizing the risk of allergic reactions and irritation. This material choice guarantees an enhanced user experience focused on comfort and safety, allowing daily use without compromising patient quality of life.</p><p>With <strong>ethylene oxide (EO)</strong> sterilization, each catheter is carefully prepared for immediate application, meeting the stringent safety standards necessary in current clinical environments. This sterilization method effectively eliminates pathogens while preserving the product material''s integrity. The catheters are <em>individually sterile</em> packaged, facilitating safe and hygienic handling in various clinical situations.</p><p>With sizes ranging from <strong>8 to 18 CH</strong>, this device is designed to accommodate a wide range of clinical needs for men. Featuring a <em>rounded tip</em>, the catheter promotes <strong>atraumatic</strong> insertion, reducing the risk of urethral trauma. The compliance with <strong>CE 0120</strong> standard highlights the commitment to quality and excellence, ensuring each catheter adheres to European medical device standards. Recognized for its <strong>single-use</strong> nature, this product prioritizes hygiene protocols and infection prevention.</p><table class="min-w-full bg-white"><thead><tr><th class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">Feature</th><th class="py-2 px-4 border-b border-gray-200">Detail</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b">Material</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b">Medical-grade silicone</td></tr><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b">Sterilization</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b">Ethylene oxide (EO)</td></tr><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b">CE / ISO Compliance</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b">CE 0120</td></tr><tr><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b">Clinical Use</td><td class="py-2 px-4 border-b">Single use</td></tr><tr><td class="py-2 px-4">Features</td><td class="py-2 px-4">Sizes 8 to 18 CH, Rounded tip</td></tr></tbody></table>' WHERE id = 517;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Coloplast Intermittent Male Catheter (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p>The Coloplast Intermittent Male Catheter (Multi-Sizes) is an advanced solution designed to offer an optimized intermittent catheterization experience. Made from high-quality medical-grade PVC, this device features exceptional biocompatibility, thus minimizing the risk of tissue reactions. The sterilization process using ethylene oxide (EO) ensures the product''s purity, eliminating all potential contaminants and ensuring maximum safety with each use.</p><p>Equipped with a hydrophilic tip, this catheter offers smoother and atraumatic insertion, reducing discomfort for the patient. Available in sizes - 14 Fr, 16 Fr, 18 Fr - it allows optimal adaptation according to the specific clinical needs of patients. Each catheter is individually sterile packaged, ensuring protection against environmental pathogens and maintaining product integrity until use.</p><p>Compliant with CE standards, this catheter meets the stringent safety and efficacy criteria required in modern clinical environments. The ergonomic design and high-quality materials used in the manufacture of the Coloplast Intermittent Male Catheter attest to Coloplast''s unwavering commitment to innovation and clinical excellence.</p><table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200"><thead class="bg-gray-50"><tr><th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Specification</th><th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Details</th></tr></thead><tbody class="bg-white divide-y divide-gray-200"><tr><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Material</td><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Medical-grade PVC</td></tr><tr><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Sterilization</td><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Ethylene oxide (EO)</td></tr><tr><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Compliance</td><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">CE</td></tr><tr><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Clinical Use</td><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Single use</td></tr><tr><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Features</td><td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap">Hydrophilic tip, sizes 14 Fr, 16 Fr, 18 Fr, sterile individual packaging</td></tr></tbody></table><p>This medical device is designed with high-quality clinical materials. Key technical features: <strong>Material</strong>: Soft PVC with hydrophilic PVP coating. <strong>Lubrication</strong>: Pre-lubricated, ready-to-use after immersion in water. <strong>Design</strong>: Fire-polished eyes for atraumatic insertion. <strong>Clinical Use</strong>: Self-intermittent catheterization (SIC), prevention of microtraumatic urethral injuries.</p>' WHERE id = 522;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Lumbar Puncture Needle (Multi-Sizes)', description_en = '<p>The Lumbar Puncture Needle (Multi-Sizes) is meticulously designed to meet the stringent demands of modern clinical practices. Constructed from 304 stainless steel, it ensures superior biocompatibility while offering outstanding durability for intensive use. This material perfectly aligns with high safety standards, thus minimizing the risk of nosocomial infections and adverse reactions.</p>

<p>Sterilized with ethylene oxide (EO), this needle guarantees impeccable sterility, essential for medical practices where patient safety is paramount. Available in various sizes from 18G to 25G, it provides maximum adaptability to meet the specific needs of each procedure.</p>

<p>Distinguished by its atraumatic bevel tip, this needle is designed to reduce tissue trauma and enhance patient comfort. Its individually sterilized packaging ensures quick and efficient preparation during urgent and critical medical procedures.</p>

