UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Wiscope 7.5 Fr Single-Use Flexible Ureteroscope', description_en = '<p>The Wiscope 7.5 Fr Single-Use Flexible Ureteroscope is designed to meet the highest clinical requirements, offering optimal flexibility and maneuverability for urological procedures. With a size of 7.5 Fr, this ureteroscope is perfectly suited for atraumatic interventions requiring high precision. The biocompatibility of polyurethane ensures a safe contact with body tissues, minimizing the risk of adverse reactions and maximizing patient comfort.</p><p>Compliant with CE standards, this medical device meets internationally recognized stringent safety and performance criteria. Its single-use design eliminates the risk of cross-contamination, ensuring impeccable hygiene during each use. Individually packaged and sterilized with ethylene oxide (EO), each unit is ready for use immediately upon opening, optimizing workflow in high-paced clinical environments.</p><p>The advanced ergonomics of this flexible ureteroscope ensure easy handling, even in complex clinical situations. Thanks to its lightweight design and optimized insertion force, healthcare professionals can focus more on the intervention and less on the equipment. In summary, the Wiscope 7.5 Fr offers a superior quality solution for the exploration and treatment of the urinary tract, perfectly suited for institutions committed to providing excellent care.</p><table class=''min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200''><thead><tr><th class=''px-6 py-3 bg-gray-50 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider''>Feature</th><th class=''px-6 py-3 bg-gray-50 text-left text-xs font-medium text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider''>Description</th></tr></thead><tbody class=''bg-white divide-y divide-gray-200''><tr><td class=''px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium text-gray-900''>Material</td><td class=''px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-gray-500''>Polyurethane</td></tr><tr><td class=''px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium text-gray-900''>Sterilization</td><td class=''px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-gray-500''>Ethylene Oxide (EO)</td></tr><tr><td class=''px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium text-gray-900''>CE / ISO Compliance</td><td class=''px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-gray-500''>CE</td></tr><tr><td class=''px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium text-gray-900''>Clinical Use</td><td class=''px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-gray-500''>Single-use</td></tr><tr><td class=''px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium text-gray-900''>Features</td><td class=''px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-gray-500''>7.5 Fr, Flexible, Ergonomic, Individually sterile packaged</td></tr></tbody></table>' WHERE id = 533;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Paramount Sterile Scalpel Blades (No. 11)', description_en = '<p>Paramount sterile stainless steel scalpel blades No. 11. Designed for precise incision and maximum safety in the operating room.</p><p>This medical device is crafted from high-quality clinical materials. Key technical features include: <strong>Material</strong>: Medical-grade Carbon Steel. <strong>Sterilization</strong>: Gamma Radiation (25 kGy). <strong>Compatibility with Handles</strong>: Handles No. 3, 3L, 5, 7. <strong>Packaging</strong>: Box of 100 units (individually wrapped in aluminum). <strong>Clinical Use</strong>: General surgery, precise incisions.</p>' WHERE id = 10006;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Paramount Sterile Scalpel Blades (No. 15)', description_en = '<p>Paramount sterile stainless steel scalpel blades No. 15. Curved design for delicate dissections.</p><p>This medical device is crafted from high-quality clinical materials. Key technical features include: <strong>Material</strong>: Medical-grade Carbon Steel. <strong>Sterilization</strong>: Gamma Radiation (25 kGy). <strong>Compatibility with Handles</strong>: Handles No. 3, 3L, 5, 7. <strong>Packaging</strong>: Box of 100 units (individually wrapped in aluminum). <strong>Clinical Use</strong>: Delicate dissections, dermatologic surgery.</p>' WHERE id = 10007;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Imaging System for Ureteroscope', description_en = '<div class="prose max-w-none"><p>The Imaging System for Ureteroscope, SKU: OTU-A, is designed to meet the highest expectations of practitioners in urology, offering a highly precise internal visualization solution for diagnostic and therapeutic procedures. Manufactured from 316L stainless steel, known for its durability and biocompatibility, this device ensures exceptional durability while minimizing the risk of adverse reactions with biological tissues.</p><p>With an HD 1080p camera resolution, the system delivers superior image quality, allowing clinicians to distinguish even the most subtle anatomical structures, thereby optimizing diagnostic efficiency. Its ergonomic design, coupled with an atraumatic insertion feature, reduces operator fatigue and potential tissue trauma during use.</p><p>In compliance with the strictest safety standards, the Imaging System is CE certified and sterilized with ethylene oxide (EO), ensuring the highest levels of hygiene. The USB-C connection simplifies integration with modern digital systems for an efficient workflow, making this ureteroscope a key component in advanced medical equipment.</p></div><table class="min-w-full bg-white"><thead><tr><th class="py-2 px-4 bg-gray-200">Specification</th><th class="py-2 px-4 bg-gray-200">Details</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="border px-4 py-2">Material</td><td class="border px-4 py-2">316L Stainless Steel</td></tr><tr><td class="border px-4 py-2">Sterilization</td><td class="border px-4 py-2">Ethylene Oxide (EO)</td></tr><tr><td class="border px-4 py-2">Compliance</td><td class="border px-4 py-2">CE Certified</td></tr><tr><td class="border px-4 py-2">Dimensions</td><td class="border px-4 py-2">150 cm Length, 5 mm Diameter</td></tr><tr><td class="border px-4 py-2">Clinical Use</td><td class="border px-4 py-2">Internal visualization during urological procedures</td></tr><tr><td class="border px-4 py-2">Features</td><td class="border px-4 py-2">HD 1080p camera resolution, USB-C connection type</td></tr></tbody></table>' WHERE id = 530;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Luer Slip Syringe - 3-Part Latex-Free Syringe - 20ml', description_en = '<p>The 20 ml Luer Slip Syringe, coded under SKU: NE176520, is a highly sophisticated medical device designed to meet the rigorous demands of modern clinical and hospital environments. Developed latex-free, this syringe minimizes allergic reaction risks, ensuring maximum biocompatibility with human tissues. Its three-part design is optimized to guarantee precise and consistent medication administration, contributing to a smooth and safe user experience for healthcare personnel.</p><p>Manufactured from polypropylene, a material known for its robustness and transparency, this syringe offers superior ergonomics, facilitating handling even during complex procedures. Sterilization by ethylene oxide (EO) ensures stringent asepsis, essential for preventing nosocomial infections. Each syringe is individually packaged, maintaining its sterile integrity until use.</p><p>CE compliance is an added guarantee of safety and performance, attesting to the commitment to the highest quality standards. As a single-use device, it is specifically suited for various clinical interventions while ensuring operational efficiency and high-level health control. The Luer Slip connector provides quick and reliable connections to associated components, maximizing usability.</p><table class="min-w-full border-collapse"><thead><tr class="border-b"><th class="px-4 py-2">Technical Characteristics</th><th class="px-4 py-2">Details</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="border-b"><td class="px-4 py-2">Material</td><td class="px-4 py-2">Latex-free Polypropylene</td></tr><tr class="border-b"><td class="px-4 py-2">Sterilization</td><td class="px-4 py-2">Ethylene Oxide (EO)</td></tr><tr class="border-b"><td class="px-4 py-2">CE / ISO Compliance</td><td class="px-4 py-2">CE Certification</td></tr><tr class="border-b"><td class="px-4 py-2">Clinical Use</td><td class="px-4 py-2">Single-use, professional in clinical and hospital settings</td></tr><tr class="border-b"><td class="px-4 py-2">Features</td><td class="px-4 py-2">Individually wrapped in sachet, Tip Type: Luer Slip</td></tr></tbody></table>' WHERE id = 561;
UPDATE product SET name_en = 'Essential Dental Care Kit', description_en = '<p>The <strong>Essential Dental Care Kit</strong> (SKU: KIT-DENT-001) is distinguished by its precision engineering and the use of top-quality materials. Specifically designed for everyday dental procedures, this kit embodies a perfect balance between functionality and clinical comfort. Each instrument is made from <em>304 Stainless Steel</em>, known for its strength and corrosion resistance, ensuring optimal biocompatibility with human tissues. The atraumatic design of the instruments enhances safety and comfort profiles during dental evaluation and treatment procedures.</p>

<p>Our kit is meticulously sterilized using <em>Ethylene Oxide (EO)</em>, providing additional safety assurance against cross-contamination. This sterilization method guarantees the microbiological purity of the instruments, making them ready for immediate use. This commitment to safety is reinforced by the <strong>CE certification</strong>, which demonstrates our compliance with stringent European medical device standards.</p>

<p>Designed for <em>single use</em>, the instruments in the Essential Dental Care Kit are individually packaged, facilitating their rapid and efficient implementation while minimizing infection risks. Each tool''s dimensions of 15 cm are specifically chosen for ergonomic balance, allowing precise handling and easy access to intraoral spaces for optimal care. Whether for use in a clinic or hospital environment, this kit aims to be the indispensable tool for any dentist committed to providing quality care to their patients.</p>

